Step 13
Step name: Creation and Configuration of WAF
#WAF is a web application firewall that lets you monitor web requests(HTTP and HTTPS) that are forwarded to to your Application Load Balancer. 
Instructions:
1) Using the ALB configure your WAF
2) Define the conditions using either cross-site scripting, SQL code injection, Geolocation, IP address conditions etc
3) Define the rules
4) Determine which set of rules and coditions that are allowed, blocked or should be counted
5) Create your WAF
